About the course:
- MySQL: CRUD, Stored procedures, Functions, Events, Triggers and implementing them on in-real-life databases
- Java: Java Persistence, mapping of the class to the tables including relationships, implementing CRUD using namedQuerries
- PHP: Creating simple forms in HTML, implementing CRUD using PHP scripts
- MongoDB and CouchDB: implementing CRUD using document-based database (pros/cons)

Database Programming course - Assigments

Assigment 1 - Working with MySQL, creating stored procedures, events, functions etc
Assigment 2 - Java Presistence, making classes and mapping them to the database, implementing relationships using JPA, creating namedQuerry-es and using them.
Assigment 3 - Making a form and the search of MySQL database using PHP depending on the input 
